        "tos_acceptance_title" to "1. Acceptance of Terms",
        "tos_acceptance_content" to "By accessing and using SmartSwine app, you agree to be bound by these Terms of Service. If you do not agree to these terms, please do not use the service.",
        "tos_description_title" to "2. Description of Service",
        "tos_description_content" to "\"SmartSwine\" provides farm management tools including, but not limited to:\n• Herd tracking and health data.\n• Financial record keeping.\n• Human Resource management.\n• AI-assisted diagnostic suggestions.\n• Market access information.",
        "tos_data_privacy_title" to "3. Data Privacy & Cloud Backup",
        "tos_data_privacy_content" to "You retain ownership of the data you input (herd data, financials, e.t.c.). \nYour farm data is stored securely using Google Firebase, while we strive to protect your data, we cannot guarantee absolute security. \nBy enabling Cloud Backup, you consent to the storage and synchronization of your data across your devices. \nWe do not sell your personal or farm data to third parties.\nYou are responsible for the accuracy of the data entered. Incorrect data in the \"Feed\" or \"Financials\" modules may result in incorrect calculations.",
        "tos_no_medical_title" to "4. No Medical or Veterinary Advice (Critical Disclaimer)",
        "tos_no_medical_content" to "The \"Feed Calculator\", \"Feed Formulator\", \"Symptoms Analyzer\" and \"Disease Finder\" features are for educational and informational purposes only.\n• The AI results are generated by algorithms and are not a substitute for professional veterinary advice, diagnosis, or treatment.\n• The User agrees to consult a licensed veterinarian before making any feeding and medical decisions regarding livestock.\n• The App Owner is not liable for any livestock loss or damages resulting from the use of the app and its features.",
        "tos_user_resp_title" to "5. User Responsibilities",
        "tos_user_resp_content" to "Users are responsible for maintaining the confidentiality of their account credentials. You are responsible for all activities that occur under your account.",
        "tos_prohibited_title" to "6. Prohibited Conduct",
        "tos_prohibited_content" to "Users agree not to:\n• Use the app for any illegal purposes.\n• Attempt to reverse engineer the application.\n• Input fraudulent financial data for the purpose of deceiving third parties.",
        "tos_availability_title" to "7. Service Availability",
        "tos_availability_content" to "We strive for 99% uptime but do not guarantee uninterrupted access to the service. Data backups are provided as a convenience; however, users are encouraged to maintain their own records.",
        "tos_liability_title" to "8. Limitation of Liability",
        "tos_liability_content" to "SmartSwine app is provided \"as is.\" To the maximum extent permitted by law, its developers shall not be liable for any direct, indirect, incidental, or consequential damages resulting from the use or inability to use the service, including livestock loss or financial discrepancies.",
        "tos_financial_data_title" to "9. Financial Data",
        "tos_financial_data_content" to "The \"Financials\" module is a tracking tool and does not constitute professional accounting or tax advice. Users are encouraged to export their data for review by certified accountants.",
        "tos_changes_title" to "10. Changes to Terms",
        "tos_changes_content" to "We reserve the right to modify these terms at any time. Continued use of the app constitutes acceptance of the new terms.",
        "tos_contact_title" to "11. Contact Information",
        "tos_contact_content" to "For support or legal inquiries, please contact the developer through the app's profile settings.",
        "contact_support" to "Contact Support: %s",
        "quote_1" to "Agriculture is the most healthful, most useful and most noble employment of man. - George Washington",
        "quote_2" to "The farmer is the only man in our economy who buys everything at retail, sells everything at wholesale, and pays the freight both ways. - John F. Kennedy",
        "quote_3" to "Farming is a profession of hope. - Brian Brett",
        "quote_4" to "The ultimate goal of farming is not the growing of crops, but the cultivation and perfection of human beings. - Masanobu Fukuoka",
        "quote_5" to "Hard work spotlights the character of people: some turn up their sleeves, some turn up their noses, and some don't turn up at all. - Sam Ewing",
        "quote_6" to "Persistence is to the character of man as carbon is to steel. - Napoleon Hill",
        "quote_7" to "Success is not final, failure is not fatal: it is the courage to continue that counts. - Winston Churchill",
        "quote_8" to "The only place where success comes before work is in the dictionary. - Vidal Sassoon",
        "quote_9" to "Don't judge each day by the harvest you reap but by the seeds that you plant. - Robert Louis Stevenson",
        "quote_10" to "The best way to predict your future is to create it. - Abraham Lincoln",
        "quote_11" to "Hard work beats talent when talent doesn't work hard. - Tim Notke",
        "quote_12" to "Farming looks mighty easy when your plow is a pencil and you're a thousand miles from the corn field. - Dwight D. Eisenhower",
        "quote_13" to "The master's eye fattens the pig. - Proverb",
        "quote_14" to "Great things are done by a series of small things brought together. - Vincent Van Gogh",
        "quote_15" to "The foundation of every state is the education of its youth. - Diogenes",
        "quote_16" to "Life on a farm is a school of patience. You can't hurry the crops or make an ox in two days. - Henri Alain",
        "quote_17" to "Farming is not just a job, it's a way of life. - Unknown",
        "quote_18" to "The goal is not to be better than the other man, but your previous self. - Dalai Lama",
        "quote_19" to "Sustainability is about the future of our children and grandchildren. - Unknown",
        "quote_20" to "The first duty of a farmer is to leave the soil better than he found it. - Unknown",
        "quote_21" to "Work hard in silence, let your success be your noise. - Frank Ocean",
        "quote_22" to "Persistence can change failure into extraordinary achievement. - Matt Biondi",
        "quote_23" to "A farmer's work is never done, but the rewards are eternal. - Unknown",
        "quote_24" to "Every day is a new opportunity to grow. - Unknown",
        "quote_25" to "Growth is never by mere chance; it is the result of forces working together. - James Cash Penney",
        "quote_26" to "The simple life is its own reward. - Unknown",
        "quote_27" to "Farmers are the backbone of the world. - Unknown",
        "quote_28" to "A field is only as good as the man who tends it. - Unknown",
        "quote_29" to "To a farmer, every seed is a promise. - Unknown",
        "quote_30" to "Faith is the bird that feels the light when the dawn is still dark. - Rabindranath Tagore",
        "quote_31" to "Success usually comes to those who are too busy to be looking for it. - Henry David Thoreau",
        "quote_32" to "There are no shortcuts to any place worth going. - Beverly Sills",
        "quote_33" to "Believe you can and you're halfway there. - Theodore Roosevelt",
        "quote_34" to "Your heart is like a garden. You can plant flowers or you can plant weeds. - Unknown",
        "quote_35" to "The discovery of agriculture was the first big step toward a civilized life. - Arthur Keith",
        "quote_36" to "Cultivators of the earth are the most valuable citizens. - Thomas Jefferson",
        "quote_37" to "The farmer has to be an optimist or he wouldn't still be a farmer. - Will Rogers",
        "quote_38" to "It is only the farmer who faithfully plants seeds in the Spring, who reaps a harvest in the Autumn. - B.C. Forbes",
        "quote_39" to "No race can prosper till it learns that there is as much dignity in tilling a field as in writing a poem. - Booker T. Washington",
        "quote_40" to "If you tickle the earth with a hoe she laughs with a harvest. - Douglas Jerrold",
        "quote_41" to "Agriculture not only gives riches to a nation, but the only riches she can call her own. - Samuel Johnson",
        "quote_42" to "The art of agriculture is the art of being a partner with God. - Unknown",
        "quote_43" to "Being a farmer means you have a great deal of patience. - Unknown",
        "quote_44" to "Everything that slows us down and forces patience, everything that sets us back into the slow cycles of nature, is a help. - May Sarton",
        "quote_45" to "The farmer is a magician who produces money from the mud. - Amit Kalantri",
        "quote_46" to "Soil is the hidden half of nature. - Unknown",
        "quote_47" to "Plowing is the foundation of agriculture. - Unknown",
        "quote_48" to "Nature does not hurry, yet everything is accomplished. - Lao Tzu",
        "quote_49" to "One who has a land has a gold. - African Proverb",
        "quote_50" to "Take care of the land and the land will take care of you. - Unknown",
        "quote_51" to "Small-scale farmers are the heroes of our food system. - Unknown",
        "quote_52" to "Persistence is the twin sister of excellence. One is a matter of quality; the other, a matter of time. - Marabel Morgan",
        "quote_53" to "Hard work is the formula for success. - Unknown",
        "quote_54" to "The sweat of the farmer is the rain for the crops. - Unknown",
        "quote_55" to "The harder you work for something, the greater you'll feel when you achieve it. - Unknown",
        "quote_56" to "Success is the sum of small efforts, repeated day in and day out. - Robert Collier",
        "quote_57" to "Dream big, work hard, stay focused. - Unknown",
        "quote_58" to "Challenges are what make life interesting and overcoming them is what makes life meaningful. - Joshua J. Marine",
        "quote_59" to "Don't wait for opportunity. Create it. - Unknown",
        "quote_60" to "The secret of getting ahead is getting started. - Mark Twain",
        "quote_61" to "Quality is not an act, it is a habit. - Aristotle",
        "quote_62" to "I find that the harder I work, the more luck I seem to have. - Thomas Jefferson",
        "quote_63" to "Strength and growth come only through continuous effort and struggle. - Napoleon Hill",
        "quote_64" to "Courage is not having the strength to go on; it is going on when you don't have the strength. - Theodore Roosevelt",
        "quote_65" to "The road to success is always under construction. - Lily Tomlin",
        "quote_66" to "Failure is the condiment that gives success its flavor. - Truman Capote",
        "quote_67" to "Do not be embarrassed by your failures, learn from them and start again. - Richard Branson",
        "quote_68" to "Hard times don't create heroes. It is during the hard times when the 'hero' within us is revealed. - Bob Riley",
        "quote_69" to "Character is the ability to carry out a good resolution long after the excitement of the moment has passed. - Cavett Robert",
        "quote_70" to "Your harvest will come if you do not give up. - Unknown",
